<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Protected or Forgotten? — NFL Player Safety Campaign</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Barlow+Condensed:wght@400;600;700;900&family=Lora:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

  :root {
    --green: #00265c;
    --green-mid: #003a8c;
    --green-light: #0055cc;
    --gold: #ffd100;
    --gold-light: #ffe24d;
    --cream: #f0f4ff;
    --dark: #00152e;
    --text: #001840;
    --muted: #3a5a8a;
  }

  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

  body {
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
    background-color: var(--dark);
    color: var(--cream);
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  /* ── HERO ── */
  .hero {
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
    position: relative;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 20% 50%, rgba(0,60,140,0.45) 0%, transparent 60%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 80% 30%, rgba(255,209,0,0.12) 0%, transparent 50%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, #00152e 0%, #001f4a 60%, #00152e 100%);
  }

  .hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(
      0deg, transparent, transparent 59px, rgba(255,255,255,0.025) 60px
    ), repeating-linear-gradient(
      90deg, transparent, transparent 59px, rgba(255,255,255,0.025) 60px
    );
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .hero-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.25em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fadeUp 0.8s ease 0.2s forwards;
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(4rem, 12vw, 9rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 0.9;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--cream);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fadeUp 0.9s ease 0.4s forwards;
  }

  .hero-title span {
    color: var(--gold);
    display: block;
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.3rem);
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.7);
    max-width: 600px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    font-style: italic;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fadeUp 0.9s ease 0.6s forwards;
  }

  .hero-cta {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--dark);
    background: var(--gold);
    padding: 0.85rem 2.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 700;
    border: 2px solid var(--gold);
    transition: background 0.2s, color 0.2s;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fadeUp 0.9s ease 0.8s forwards;
  }

  .hero-cta:hover {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  /* ── STAT STRIP ── */
  .stat-strip {
    background: var(--gold);
    padding: 2rem 4rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-around;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .stat-item {
    text-align: center;
    color: #00152e;
  }

  .stat-number {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1;
    display: block;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    display: block;
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  /* ── SECTIONS ── */
  section {
    padding: 6rem 2rem;
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.25em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--cream);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .section-title em {
    color: var(--gold);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .section-body {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.8);
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  /* ── ISSUE CARDS ── */
  .issues-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .issue-card {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(201,168,76,0.2);
    padding: 2rem;
    position: relative;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, background 0.2s;
  }

  .issue-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(201,168,76,0.5);
    background: rgba(201,168,76,0.05);
  }

  .issue-card::before {
    content: attr(data-num);
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 5rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: rgba(201,168,76,0.08);
    position: absolute;
    top: 0.5rem;
    right: 1rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .issue-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold-light);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .issue-card p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.7);
  }

  /* ── QUOTE BLOCK ── */
  .quote-section {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00265c 0%, #00152e 100%);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
    padding: 4rem 5rem;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  .quote-section blockquote {
    font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 3vw, 1.8rem);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--cream);
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .quote-section cite {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-style: normal;
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* ── DIVIDER ── */
  .divider {
    width: 60px;
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--gold);
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
  }

  /* ── DEMANDS ── */
  .demands-list {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .demand-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(201,168,76,0.15);
  }

  .demand-icon {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--gold);
    min-width: 2.5rem;
    padding-top: 0.1rem;
  }

  .demand-text h4 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--cream);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .demand-text p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.65);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ── REFERENCES ── */
  .references-section {
    background: #000d1a;
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
  }

  .references-inner {
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .references-section h2 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .references-section p.ref-intro {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.5);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .ref-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .ref-entry {
    border-left: 2px solid rgba(201,168,76,0.3);
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.65);
    line-height: 1.6;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .ref-entry:hover {
    border-color: var(--gold);
  }

  .ref-entry a {
    color: var(--gold-light);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    word-break: break-all;
  }

  .ref-entry a:hover {
    color: var(--cream);
  }

  /* ── FOOTER ── */
  footer {
    background: var(--dark);
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.3);
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(201,168,76,0.1);
  }

  /* ── NAV ── */
  nav {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    width: 100%;
    z-index: 100;
    padding: 1.25rem 2.5rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    background: rgba(0,38,92,0.95);
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,209,0,0.3);
  }

  .nav-brand {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .nav-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .nav-links a {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,0.6);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .nav-links a:hover { color: var(--gold); }

  @keyframes fadeUp {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  .fade-in {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(24px);
    transition: opacity 0.7s ease, transform 0.7s ease;
  }

  .fade-in.visible {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .nav-links { display: none; }
    .quote-section { padding: 3rem 2rem; }
    .stat-strip { padding: 2rem; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<nav>
  <a class="nav-brand" href="#">Protected or Forgotten</a>
  <ul class="nav-links">
    <li><a href="#issues">The Issues</a></li>
    <li><a href="#demands">What Must Change</a></li>
    <li><a href="#references">Sources</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>

<!-- HERO -->
<div class="hero">
  <p class="hero-eyebrow">A Player Safety Campaign</p>
  <h1 class="hero-title">Protected<span>or Forgotten?</span></h1>
  <p class="hero-subtitle">The NFL profits billions from its players' bodies. But when careers end, who protects the players from what the game leaves behind?</p>
  <p style="font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif; font-size: 0.95rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(201,168,76,0.6); margin-bottom: 2rem; opacity: 0; animation: fadeUp 0.9s ease 0.75s forwards;">By Dominic Reider</p>
  <a class="hero-cta" href="#issues">See the Evidence</a>
</div>

<!-- STAT STRIP -->
<div class="stat-strip">
  <div class="stat-item">
    <span class="stat-number">110</span>
    <span class="stat-label">of 111 deceased NFL players had CTE</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-item">
    <span class="stat-number">$20B+</span>
    <span class="stat-label">NFL annual revenue</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-item">
    <span class="stat-number">3.3 yrs</span>
    <span class="stat-label">Average NFL career length</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-item">
    <span class="stat-number">?</span>
    <span class="stat-label">Actual concussions unreported</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ISSUES -->
<section id="issues">
  <p class="section-label fade-in">The Problem</p>
  <h2 class="section-title fade-in">Four Reasons the <em>NFL Is Failing</em> Its Players</h2>
  <div class="divider fade-in"></div>
  <p class="section-body fade-in">Research consistently shows that NFL players face serious, long-term health consequences — and the league's current systems do not go far enough to prevent or address them.</p>

  <div class="issues-grid">
    <div class="issue-card fade-in" data-num="01">
      <h3>Unequal Bargaining Power</h3>
      <p>Because football carries extreme injury risk, players have less negotiating power than athletes in other leagues. They accept unsafe conditions because the financial stakes leave them no real choice.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="issue-card fade-in" data-num="02">
      <h3>Hidden Concussion Data</h3>
      <p>Official NFL concussion numbers don't tell the full story. Critics argue the data underrepresents true head trauma levels, masking the real scope of neurological damage players experience.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="issue-card fade-in" data-num="03">
      <h3>Preventable Field Risks</h3>
      <p>Studies show that playing surface — turf vs. natural grass — directly affects injury rates. The NFL has more control over player safety conditions than it publicly acknowledges.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="issue-card fade-in" data-num="04">
      <h3>Unequal Risk & Pay</h3>
      <p>Injury risk and concussion exposure are not evenly distributed across positions. Players who take the most physical punishment are not always compensated or protected proportionally.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- QUOTE BLOCK -->
<div class="quote-section">
  <blockquote>
    "CTE is a progressive neurodegenerative disease associated with repetitive head impacts — and its effects grow worse over time, often years after a player's career has ended."
    <cite>— McKee et al., 2016 &nbsp;|&nbsp; Chronic Traumatic Encephalopathy Research</cite>
  </blockquote>
</div>

<!-- WHAT MUST CHANGE -->
<section id="demands">
  <p class="section-label fade-in">The Solution</p>
  <h2 class="section-title fade-in">What the NFL <em>Must Do</em></h2>
  <div class="divider fade-in"></div>
  <p class="section-body fade-in">Progress has been made — but it is not enough. These are the changes that must happen to truly protect players, during their careers and long after.</p>

  <div class="demands-list">
    <div class="demand-item fade-in">
      <div class="demand-icon">01</div>
      <div class="demand-text">
        <h4>Improve Injury Tracking & Transparent Reporting</h4>
        <p>Concussion statistics must be independently verified and made fully public. Players, researchers, and fans deserve accurate data — not numbers shaped by the league's financial interests.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="demand-item fade-in">
      <div class="demand-icon">02</div>
      <div class="demand-text">
        <h4>Safer Playing Conditions</h4>
        <p>Field surfaces, equipment standards, and game protocols must be continuously evaluated. Evidence links artificial turf to higher injury rates — the NFL must act on that evidence.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="demand-item fade-in">
      <div class="demand-icon">03</div>
      <div class="demand-text">
        <h4>Long-Term Healthcare for Former Players</h4>
        <p>Career-ending injuries don't end when a player's contract does. The NFL must fund comprehensive, long-term medical monitoring and healthcare for former players dealing with conditions caused by the game.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="demand-item fade-in">
      <div class="demand-icon">04</div>
      <div class="demand-text">
        <h4>Fair Compensation for High-Risk Positions</h4>
        <p>Players who absorb the most physical punishment must receive pay and protection that genuinely reflects that risk — not contracts shaped by a system where injury fear reduces their bargaining power.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

